-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1438,\"repo\":\"TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-26T20:57:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/sw-toolbox/\">sw-toolbox</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/sw-toolbox/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.7k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3656,\"repo\":\"GoogleChrome/sw-toolbox\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A collection of simple helpers to simplify implementing common runtime caching patterns.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-02T16:07:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/sw-precache/\">sw-precache</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/sw-precache/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5291,\"repo\":\"GoogleChrome/sw-precache\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Generates a service worker to cache your local App Shell resources.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-02T16:07:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jCKZDTtUA2A\">Instant Loading with Service Workers (Chrome Dev Summit 2015)</a> - Explains how to structure your web app to optimize load time for initial and return visitors, and cover helpful service worker libraries that minimize the amount of boilerplate code you'll have to write.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-02T16:07:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Case Studies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/web/showcase/2016/service-worker-perf\">Measuring the Real-world Performance Impact of Service Workers</a> - One of the most significant benefits of service workers (from a performance perspective, at least) is their ability to proactively control the caching of assets. A web application that can cache all of its necessary resources should load substantially faster for returning visitors. But what do these gains actually look like to real users? And how do you even measure this?</li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-02T16:07:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Related Technologies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps#background-sync\">Background Sync</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps#background-sync\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1438,\"repo\":\"TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-17T08:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://brucelawson.github.io/manifest/\">Manifest Generator</a> - Generate a web app manifest, required for push notifications and installable web apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-09T18:46:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Case Studies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/web/showcase/case-study/service-workers-iowa\">Service Workers in Production</a> - A case-study about how Google I/O 2015 web app was built.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-08T09:09:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://remysharp.com/2016/03/22/the-copy--paste-guide-to-your-first-service-worker\">The copy &#x26; paste guide to your first Service Worker</a> - Shortest available introduction, by <a href=\"https://github.com/remy\">Remy Sharp</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T13:37:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Must Reads</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/slightlyoff/ServiceWorker/blob/master/explainer.md\">Service Workers Explained</a> - Service workers explained by <a href=\"https://github.com/slightlyoff\">Alex Russell</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dev.opera.com/articles/offline-with-upup-service-workers/\">Building Offline Sites with ServiceWorkers and UpUp</a> - A general introduction to service workers and using UpUp to provide offline functionality in minutes.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/delapuente/service-workers-101\">Service Workers 101</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/delapuente/service-workers-101\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">689</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":689,\"repo\":\"delapuente/service-workers-101\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An infographic summarizing the most important parts of service workers API.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jakearchibald.com/2014/offline-cookbook/\">The offline cookbook</a> - The bible of service worker Patterns by Jake Archibald.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/service-workers/\">Service Workers - W3C Specification</a> - The official service workers spec.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://upup.rocks/\">UpUp</a> - A popular service worker library providing complete offline functionality for your site in 1 line of code.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.udacity.com/course/offline-web-applications--ud899\">Offline Web Applications Using IndexedDB &#x26; Service Worker</a> - This free Udacity course is a must if you're planning to dive deep into service workers.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T12:22:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Browser Support</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://caniuse.com/#feat=serviceworkers\">Can I Use - Service Workers</a> - Up-to-date browser support table of ServiceWorker API.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T11:44:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Browser Support</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jakearchibald.github.io/isserviceworkerready/\">Jake Archibald - Is Service Worker ready?</a> - Current status of ServiceWorker support in different browsers.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T11:44:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/service-worker/introduction/\">Introduction to Service Worker</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-07T11:15:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/cmGr0RszHc8\">Instant Loading: Building offline-first Progressive Web Apps - Google I/O 2016</a> - A quick dive into the most common technologies and techniques for building progressive web apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-05-29T19:44:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Reference</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wicg.github.io/BackgroundSync/spec/\">Background Sync Spec</a> - The WIP spec for Background Sync.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-17T15:53:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://serviceworke.rs/\">ServiceWorker Cookbook by Mozilla</a> - A collection of recipes for different use cases.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-14T13:40:53.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/nikgraf/awesome-draft-js","repo":"nikgraf/awesome-draft-js"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps","repo":"TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps"}},"pageContext":{"type":"week","repo":"TalAter/awesome-service-workers","id":"awesomes/github.com/TalAter/awesome-service-workers","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/nikgraf/awesome-draft-js","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/TalAter/awesome-progressive-web-apps"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","3289010534"]}